            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EPride%20is%20undoubtedly%20the%20deadliest%20of%20sins.%20It%20caused%20the%20downfall%20of%20Satan%2C%20and%20for%20centuries%20he%20has%20deceived%20countless%20men%20and%20women.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EDavid%2C%20the%20greatest%20king%20of%20Israel%2C%20would%20not%20allow%20pride%20in%20his%20life.%20He%20declared%2C%20%22Lord%2C%20my%20heart%20is%20not%20proud%3B%20my%20eyes%20are%20not%20haughty.%20I%20don't%20concern%20myself%20with%20matters%20too%20great%20or%20awesome%20for%20me%22%20(Psalm%20131%3A1).%20Associating%20with%20the%20wealthy%2C%20the%20intellectual%2C%20or%20political%20%22movers%20and%20shakers%22%20causes%20some%20to%20consider%20themselves%20exalted%2C%20as%20did%20Haman%20in%20the%20book%20of%20Esther.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EDavid%2C%20however%2C%20was%20willing%20to%20associate%20with%20anyone%20and%20still%20remained%20secure%20in%20who%20he%20was.%20He%20reminded%20himself%20that%20his%20soul%20was%20as%20quiet%20as%20a%20%22weaned%20child%20with%20its%20mother%22%20(v.%202%2C%20NIV).%20Weaned%20children%20do%20not%20struggle%20for%20position%20and%20nourishment%2C%20but%20rather%20are%20relaxed%20and%20content%20to%20lie%20on%20their%20mothers'%20laps.%20Prideful%20people%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20are%20always%20fidgety.%20They%20push%20for%20position%20and%20notoriety%20and%20work%20all%20the%20angles.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EAs%20though%20we%20were%20babies%20on%20God's%20lap%2C%20let%20us%20relax%20and%20allow%20Him%20to%20exalt%20us.%20We%20will%20live%20longer%20and%20go%20further%20as%20well!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
